ouse gas emissions in owned and operated facilities globally and to divert  of the waste from landfill for our us facilities resources customer bill of rights franchise information gap inc policies factory list careers behind the scenes apply for a job keep in touch contact us email alerts adressed blog twitter facebook youtube instagram linkedin contact us  terms of use  privacy policy   gap inc all rights reserved gap inc  wikipedia gap inc from wikipedia the free encyclopedia   redirected from gap clothing retailer jump to navigation search gap inc gap inc headquarters building type public traded as nyse gps sp  component industry retail founded august    years ago  san francisco california us founder donald fisher doris f fisher headquarters san francisco california us number of locations  q   us  area served worldwide key people art peck ceo bob fisher chairman products clothing accessories revenue us  billion  us  billion  operating income us  billion  us  billion  net income us  billion  us  billion  total assets us  billion  us  billion  total equity us  billion  us  billion  number of employees  may  subsidiaries banana republic old navy athleta intermix website wwwgapinccomcontentgapinchtmlhtml the gap inc commonly known as gap inc or gap stylized as gap is an american worldwide clothing and accessories retailer it was founded in  by donald fisher and doris f fisher and is headquartered in san francisco california the company operates five primary divisions the namesake banner banana republic old navy intermix and athleta gap inc is the largest specialty retailer in the united states and is rd in total international locations behind inditex group and hm as of september  the company has approximately  employees and operates  stores worldwide of which  are located in the us the fisher family remains deeply involved in the company collectively owning much of its stock donald fisher served as chairman of the board until  playing a role in the ouster of thenceo millard drexler in  and remained on the board until his death on september   fishers wife and their son robert j fisher also serve on gaps board of directors robert succeeded his father as chairman in  and also served as ceo on an interim basis following the resignation of paul pressler in  before being succeeded by glenn k murphy up until  on february   art peck took over as ceo contents  history  corporate identity  logo  brands  marketing  international presence  product red  labour controversies  management  leadership  board of directors  stores  restatement  see also  references  external links historyedit donald and doris fisher who had a difficult time finding jeans that fit opened the first gap store on ocean avenue in san francisco on august   its merchandise consisted of levis and lp records they had raised us to open the store and reached us million in sales in the second full year of operation in  gap opened its second store in san jose california its back room serves as the companys first replenishment warehouse in  gap established its corporate headquarters in burlingame california with four employees by  the company had over  locations and had expanded into the east coast market with a store in the echelon mall in voorhees new jersey in  gap began to sell privatelabel merchandise in the s gap assumed an upscale identity and revamped its inventory under the direction of millard drexler however drexler was removed from his position after  years of service in  after overexpansion a month slump in sales and tensions with the fisher family drexler refused to sign a noncompete agreement and eventually became ceo of j crew one month after his departure merchandise that he had ordered was responsible for a strong rebound in sales robert j fisher recruited paul pressler as the new ceo he was credited with closing underperforming locations and paying off debt however his focus groups failed to recover the companys leadership in its market in  gap announced that it would focus its efforts on recruiting a chief executive officer who has deep retailing and merchandising experience ideally in apparel understands the creative process and can effectively execute strategies in large complex environments while maintaining strong financial discipline that january pressler resigned after two disappointing holiday sales seasons and was succeeded by robert j fisher on an interim basis he began working with the company in  and joined the board in  and would later assume several senior executive positions including president of banana republic and the gap units the boards search committee was led by adrian bellamy chairman of the body shop international and included founder donald fisher on february  marka hansen the former head of the banana republic division replaced cynthia harriss as the leader of the gap division the executive president for marketing and merchandising jack calhoun became interim president of banana republic in may old navy laid off approximately  managers in lower volume locations to help streamline costs that july glenn murphy previously ceo of shoppers drug mart in canada was announced as the new ceo of gap inc new lead designers were also brought on board to help define a fashionable image including patrick robinson for gap adult simon kneen for banana republic and todd oldham for old navy robinson was hired as chief designer in  but was dismissed in may  after sales failed to increase however he enjoyed commercial success in international markets in october  gap inc announced plans to close  us stores nearly  percent by the end of  however it also plans to expand its presence in china the company announced it would open its first stores in brazil in the fall of  in january  gap inc announced plans to close their subsidiary piperlime in order to focus on their core brands the first and only piperlime store based in soho new york city closed in april corporate identityedit logoedit gap inc owns a trademark to its name gap the gaps original trademark was a service mark for retail clothing store services the application was filed with the united states patent and trademark office on february   by the gap stores registration was granted on october   the first use of the trademark was on august   and expanded to commercial usage on october   a second application was filed by gap stores inc on september   this time for a trademark filed for shirts the first usage for shirts and clothing products was on june   trademark registration was granted on december   both the service mark and trademark are registered and owned by gap apparel llc of san francisco california on october   in an effort to establish a contemporary presence gap introduced a new logo it was designed with the helvetica font and reduced the prominence of the brands iconic blue box after much public outcry the company reverted to its previous blue box logo on october  after less than a week in use marka hansen the executive who oversaw the logo change resigned february   – – october –  reverted due to strong dislike –present brandsedit banana republic a small safarithemed clothing retailer was purchased by gap in  and was rebranded as an upscale clothing retailer in the late s old navy was launched in  as a value chain with a specialty flair forth  towne the companys fourth traditional retail concept was launched on august   featuring apparel targeted toward women  years and older on february   after an month trial period it was discontinued and the  stores were closed a fifth brand the online clothing and accessories retailer piperlime was created in  however as of april  the brand has been retired a sixth brand athleta a womens athletic wear line was added in  intermix a multibrand fashion retailer founded in  was acquired by gap inc in  gaps sales by division in q  divisions total revenue gap north america  million banana republic north america  million old navy north america  billion international  million gap inc direct  million marketingedit a gap location in westfield valley fair san jose ca the gap originally targeted the younger generation when it opened with its name referring to the generation gap of the time it originally sold everything that levi strauss  co made in every style size and color and organized the stock by size the gap was the first of many shops that carried only levis in  gap started making their own jeans as a way to differentiate themselves from department stores gaps current marketing works to appeal to a broad demographic of customers whereas banana republic presents a sophisticated image and old navy focuses fun fashion and value for families and younger customers while the company has been criticized for blandness and uniformity in its selling environments it maintains that it tailors its stores to appeal to unique markets by developing multiple formats and designs the domain wwwgapcom attracts over  million visitors annually according to a  competecom survey the brand is being criticized in the uk because the merchandise that is offered to the uk customers cost double the prices or even a direct £ swap found in the united states gap also does not offer xxl or larger sizes in the uk stating the uk market does not require them in contrast to market leader next who offer a variety of larger sizes in the uk international presenceedit gap in hillcrest mall gap operates companyowned stores in the united states canada the united kingdom france italy indonesia japan china hong kong taiwan and mexico as of may  it also has franchise agreements with unaffiliated franchisees to operate gap banana republic or old navy stores in  countries as of may  gap inc operates  companyowned and franchise locations in january  gap signed a deal with marinopoulos group to open gap and banana republic stores in greece romania bulgaria cyprus and croatia in february  elbit imaging ltd secured a franchise to open and operate gap and banana republic stores in israel in august  the company opened its first store in melbourne australia at chadstone shopping centrecitation needed in september  komax opened the first gap store in chile due to a franchise in october  the first gap store opened in warsaw poland but shut it down and two other locations in wrocław and katowice in  gap now has a store in new delhi india which opened in may  on  february  gap launched stores in mumbai at oberoi mall and infinity in may  gap inc announced it would shutter all old navy stores in japan in response to poor q performance for old navy and consistent losses across the organization in  gap closed all its stores in israel product rededit this section does not cite any sources please help improve this section by adding citations to reliable sources unsourced material may be challenged and removed march  learn how and when to remove this template message in  gap took part in the product red campaign with the launch of a special red collection including a tshirt manufactured in lesotho from african cotton the expanded gap product red collection was released on october    to  percent of the profits went to the global fund depending on the item the company continued the products into  especially in the lead up to valentines day using slogans such as admired and desired national labor committee for worker and human rights activists criticized gaps partnerships because gap has historically been accused of sweatshoplike conditions product red has contributed over  million to the global fund more than any other private donation received to date other launch partners included american express apple inc converse hallmark emporio armani and motorola labour controversiesedit in  a class action lawsuit against gap and  other companies alleged that sweatshop workers in saipan were not paid for overtime work were subjected to forced abortion and were required to work in unsafe working conditions a settlement of  million dollars was reached whereby the gap did not admit liability in  ethisphere magazine chose gap from among thousands of companies evaluated as one of  worlds most ethical companies in may  adult and child employees of western a supplier in jordan were found to have worked up to  hours per week and to have gone six months without being paid some employees claimed they had been raped by managers most of these allegations were directed at walmart who mostly ignored the claims while gap immediately looked into the matter to remedy the situationnot in citation given on october   bbc footage showed child labor in indian gap factories the company denied knowledge of the happenings it subsequently removed and destroyed the single piece of clothing in question a smock blouse from a british store gap promised to investigate breaches in its ethical policy bangladeshi and international labor groups in  put forth a detailed safety proposal which entailed the establishment of independent inspections of garment factories the plan called for inspectors to have the power to close unsafe factories the proposal entailed a legally binding contract between suppliers customers and unions at a meeting in  in dhaka major european and north american retailers including gap rejected the proposal further efforts by unions to advance the proposal after numerous and deadly factory fires have been rejected after the  savar building collapse kohls became a founding member of the alliance for bangladesh worker safety on february   glenn murphy ceo of gap inc announced gap will raise the minimum wages for its  us store employees managementedit leadershipedit the current leadership is art peck chief executive officer teri liststoll evp and cfo jeff kirwan president  ceo gap mark breitbard president  ceo banana republic sonia syngal president  ceo old navy nancy green president and ceo athleta jyothi rao president and general manager intermix abinta malik evp and general manager greater china julie gruber evp general counsel corporate secretary chief compliance officer gap inc bobbi silten evp global talent  responsibility gap inc sebastian digrande evp strategy  chief customer officer gap inc paul chapman evp and chief information officer gap inc michael yee evp global supply chain sourcing and production gap inc shawn curran evp global supply chain logistics and product operations gap inc board of directorsedit domenico de sole doris f fisher  robert j fisher  chairman  chairman  william s fisher tracy gardner effective november   bella goren bob l martin jorge p montoya art peck mayo a shattuck iii katherine tsang padmasree warrior storesedit a branch on briggate in leeds west yorkshire as of the end of q  gap inc had  companyoperated or franchised stores in operation across  countries and had the ability to ship to  countries stores in brazil canada china france italy ireland japan uk and us including puerto rico are companyowned those outside of these countries are owned and operated by franchises gap   united states   japan   peoples republic of china   united kingdom   canada   mexico   france   turkey   south korea   saudi arabia   russia   spain   philippines   italy   taiwan   united arab emirates   brazil   south africa   thailand   greece   india   israel   uruguay   malaysia   vietnam   australia   chile   puerto rico   indonesia   egypt   ireland   singapore   ukraine   colombia   hong kong   kazakhstan   panama   peru   jordan   kuwait   lebanon   qatar   bahrain   armenia   austria   azerbaijan   croatia   cyprus   georgia   morocco   oman   pakistan   paraguay  banana republic   united states   canada   japan   mexico   united kingdom   south korea   turkey   thailand   puerto rico   united arab emirates   chile   indonesia   peru   philippines   saudi arabia   malaysia   panama   singapore   colombia   croatia   france   georgia   italy   kuwait   morocco   qatar  old navy   united states   canada   japan   peoples republic of china   mexico   puerto rico   philippines   saudi arabia   