o a  competecom survey the brand is being criticized in the uk because the merchandise that is offered to the uk customers cost double the prices or even a direct £ swap found in the united states gap also does not offer xxl or larger sizes in the uk stating the uk market does not require them in contrast to market leader next who offer a variety of larger sizes in the uk international presenceedit gap in hillcrest mall gap operates companyowned stores in the united states canada the united kingdom france italy indonesia japan china hong kong taiwan and mexico as of may  it also has franchise agreements with unaffiliated franchisees to operate gap banana republic or old navy stores in  countries as of may  gap inc operates  companyowned and franchise locations in january  gap signed a deal with marinopoulos group to open gap and banana republic stores in greece romania bulgaria cyprus and croatia in february  elbit imaging ltd secured a franchise to open and operate gap and banana republic stores in israel in august  the company opened its first store in melbourne australia at chadstone shopping centrecitation needed in september  komax opened the first gap store in chile due to a franchise in october  the first gap store opened in warsaw poland but shut it down and two other locations in wrocław and katowice in  gap now has a store in new delhi india which opened in may  on  february  gap launched stores in mumbai at oberoi mall and infinity in may  gap inc announced it would shutter all old navy stores in japan in response to poor q performance for old navy and consistent losses across the organization in  gap closed all its stores in israel product rededit this section does not cite any sources please help improve this section by adding citations to reliable sources unsourced material may be challenged and removed march  learn how and when to remove this template message in  gap took part in the product red campaign with the launch of a special red collection including a tshirt manufactured in lesotho from african cotton the expanded gap product red collection was released on october    to  percent of the profits went to the global fund depending on the item the company continued the products into  especially in the lead up to valentines day using slogans such as admired and desired national labor committee for worker and human rights activists criticized gaps partnerships because gap has historically been accused of sweatshoplike conditions product red has contributed over  million to the global fund more than any other private donation received to date other launch partners included american express apple inc converse hallmark emporio armani and motorola labour controversiesedit in  a class action lawsuit against gap and  other companies alleged that sweatshop workers in saipan were not paid for overtime work were subjected to forced abortion and were required to work in unsafe working conditions a settlement of  million dollars was reached whereby the gap did not admit liability in  ethisphere magazine chose gap from among thousands of companies evaluated as one of  worlds most ethical companies in may  adult and child employees of western a supplier in jordan were found to have worked up to  hours per week and to have gone six months without being paid some employees claimed they had been raped by managers most of these allegations were directed at walmart who mostly ignored the claims while gap immediately looked into the matter to remedy the situationnot in citation given on october   bbc footage showed child labor in indian gap factories the company denied knowledge of the happenings it subsequently removed and destroyed the single piece of clothing in question a smock blouse from a british store gap promised to investigate breaches in its ethical policy bangladeshi and international labor groups in  put forth a detailed safety proposal which entailed the establishment of independent inspections of garment factories the plan called for inspectors to have the power to close unsafe factories the proposal entailed a legally binding contract between suppliers customers and unions at a meeting in  in dhaka major european and north american retailers including gap rejected the proposal further efforts by unions to advance the proposal after numerous and deadly factory fires have been rejected after the  savar building collapse kohls became a founding member of the alliance for bangladesh worker safety on february   glenn murphy ceo of gap inc announced gap will raise the minimum wages for its  us store employees managementedit leadershipedit the current leadership is art peck chief executive officer teri liststoll evp and cfo jeff kirwan president  ceo gap mark breitbard president  ceo banana republic sonia syngal president  ceo old navy nancy green president and ceo athleta jyothi rao president and general manager intermix abinta malik evp and general manager greater china julie gruber evp general counsel corporate secretary chief compliance officer gap inc bobbi silten evp global talent  responsibility gap inc sebastian digrande evp strategy  chief customer officer gap inc paul chapman evp and chief information officer gap inc michael yee evp global supply chain sourcing and production gap inc shawn curran evp global supply chain logistics and product operations gap inc board of directorsedit domenico de sole doris f fisher  robert j fisher  chairman  chairman  william s fisher tracy gardner effective november   bella goren bob l martin jorge p montoya art peck mayo a shattuck iii katherine tsang padmasree warrior storesedit a branch on briggate in leeds west yorkshire as of the end of q  gap inc had  companyoperated or franchised stores in operation across  countries and had the ability to ship to  countries stores in brazil canada china france italy ireland japan uk and us including puerto rico are companyowned those outside of these countries are owned and operated by franchises